                <p>Course enrollment is straightforward:</p>
                <ol>
                  <li>Browse our course catalog or use the search function</li>
                  <li>Click on a course to view detailed information</li>
                  <li>Review prerequisites and course requirements</li>
                  <li>Click "Enroll Now" and proceed to checkout</li>
                  <li>Complete payment through our secure Stripe integration</li>
                  <li>Access your course immediately in your dashboard</li>
                </ol>
              </div>
            </details>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item" id="course-access">
            <h3 class="faq-category">Course Access</h3>
            
            <details class="faq-question">
              <summary>How do I access my purchased courses?</summary>
              <div class="faq-answer">
                <p>After purchasing a course:</p>
                <ol>
                  <li>Log into your account</li>
                  <li>Go to "My Dashboard" from the account menu</li>
                  <li>Find your course in the "Current Courses" section</li>
                  <li>Click "Continue Learning" to access the embedded course player</li>
                </ol>
                <p>Your progress is automatically saved as you complete lessons.</p>
              </div>
            </details>

            <details class="faq-question">
              <summary>What are the technical requirements for course access?</summary>
              <div class="faq-answer">
                <p>To ensure the best learning experience:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li><strong>Browser:</strong> Chrome 90+, Firefox 88+, Safari 14+, Edge 90+</li>
                  <li><strong>Internet:</strong> Stable broadband connection (5+ Mbps recommended)</li>
                  <li><strong>Audio:</strong> Speakers or headphones for video content</li>
                  <li><strong>JavaScript:</strong> Must be enabled</li>
                  <li><strong>Cookies:</strong> Must be enabled for progress tracking</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Mobile devices are supported, but desktop/laptop recommended for optimal experience.</p>
              </div>
            </details>

            <details class="faq-question">
              <summary>Can I download courses for offline viewing?</summary>
              <div class="faq-answer">
                <p>Currently, our courses are designed for online access only to ensure:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>Real-time progress tracking and reporting</li>
                  <li>Up-to-date content and safety regulations</li>
                  <li>Interactive elements and assessments</li>
                  <li>Secure access and content protection</li>
                </ul>
                <p>However, downloadable resources like PDFs and reference materials are available for each course.</p>
              </div>
            </details>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item" id="certificates">
            <h3 class="faq-category">Certificates & CEUs</h3>
            
            <details class="faq-question">
              <summary>How do I receive my certificate after completing a course?</summary>
              <div class="faq-answer">
                <p>Certificate generation is automatic:</p>
                <ol>
                  <li>Complete all required course modules and assessments</li>
                  <li>Achieve the minimum passing score (typically 80%)</li>
                  <li>Your certificate is automatically generated and available in your dashboard</li>
                  <li>Download as PDF or share directly to LinkedIn</li>
                </ol>
                <p>Certificates include your name, course completion date, CEU credits earned, and verification QR code.</p>
              </div>
            </details>

            <details class="faq-question">
              <summary>Are AAI certificates recognized by industry organizations?</summary>
              <div class="faq-answer">
                <p>Yes, AAI certificates are widely recognized:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li><strong>IAAPA:</strong> Member organization with accredited training programs</li>
                  <li><strong>ASTM F24:</strong> Course content aligned with F24 committee standards</li>
                  <li><strong>NAARSO:</strong> Approved continuing education provider</li>
                  <li><strong>State Agencies:</strong> Accepted by most state inspection departments</li>
                  <li><strong>Insurance Providers:</strong> Recognized for premium discounts</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Each certificate includes verification information for employers and regulators.</p>
              </div>
            </details>

            <details class="faq-question">
              <summary>How do CEU credits work?</summary>
              <div class="faq-answer">
                <p>Continuing Education Units (CEUs) are earned based on course completion:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li><strong>1 CEU = 10 contact hours</strong> of professional education</li>
                  <li>Credits are automatically calculated based on course length</li>
                  <li>Your transcript maintains a permanent record of all earned CEUs</li>
                  <li>Certificates display total CEU credits for the specific course</li>
                  <li>Annual CEU summaries available for license renewal requirements</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </details>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item" id="account">
            <h3 class="faq-category">Account Support</h3>
            
            <details class="faq-question">
              <summary>How do I update my profile information?</summary>
              <div class="faq-answer">
                <p>To update your profile:</p>
                <ol>
                  <li>Log into your account</li>
                  <li>Click on your name in the top right corner</li>
                  <li>Select "Account Settings"</li>
                  <li>Update any information in the "Profile" section</li>
                  <li>Save changes</li>
                </ol>
                <p>Note: Name changes may require verification for certificate accuracy.</p>
              </div>
            </details>

            <details class="faq-question">
              <summary>What payment methods do you accept?</summary>
              <div class="faq-answer">
                <p>We accept all major payment methods through Stripe:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>Credit cards (Visa, MasterCard, American Express, Discover)</li>
                  <li>Debit cards</li>
                  <li>Corporate credit cards</li>
                  <li>ACH bank transfers (for corporate accounts)</li>
                  <li>Purchase orders (pre-approved corporate accounts only)</li>
                </ul>
                <p>All transactions are secure and encrypted.</p>
              </div>
            </details>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item" id="technical">
            <h3 class="faq-category">Technical Issues</h3>
            
            <details class="faq-question">
              <summary>What should I do if videos won't play?</summary>
              <div class="faq-answer">
                <p>If you're experiencing video playback issues:</p>
                <ol>
                  <li>Check your internet connection speed</li>
                  <li>Clear your browser cache and cookies</li>
                  <li>Disable browser extensions temporarily</li>
                  <li>Try a different browser</li>
                  <li>Ensure JavaScript is enabled</li>
                  <li>Check if your firewall is blocking video content</li>
                </ol>
                <p>If issues persist, contact our technical support team with your browser and operating system details.</p>
              </div>
            </details>

            <details class="faq-question">
              <summary>Why is my course progress not saving?</summary>
              <div class="faq-answer">
                <p>Progress tracking requires:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>Cookies enabled in your browser</li>
                  <li>Stable internet connection during lesson completion</li>
                  <li>Completing lessons in the intended sequence</li>
                  <li>Not opening the same course in multiple browser tabs</li>
                </ul>
                <p>If progress still isn't saving, try logging out and back in, or contact support.</p>
              </div>
            </details>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item" id="corporate">
            <h3 class="faq-category">Corporate Training</h3>
            
